OL,3,CTrump, rough sleeping, and the King:
OL,4,CAndy Burnham's first day in office
OL,6,FHe went on to promise to deliver "a
OL,7,Fnew political model and a new economic
OL,8,Fmodel" for Britain.
OL,10,FRachel Reeves was axed as chancellor,
OL,11,FSir Keir's deputy prime minister David
OL,12,FLammy was sacked and Peter Kyle lost
OL,13,Fhis job as business secretary as Mr
OL,14,FBurnham cleared the way for his own
OL,15,Fallies to take key roles.
OL,17,FStarmer loyalist Steve Reed, who lost
OL,18,Fhis Cabinet role at the housing
OL,19,Fministry, told Mr Burnham: "I hope
OL,20,Fthose who did not show loyalty to Keir
OL,21,Fwill now show it to you."
OL,26,@nD@bOUpD@FO]{D@\OU}D@YO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
